The Honor 10 Lite has been launched in South Africa. Honor has powered its 10 Lite smartphone with an octa-core Kirin 710 chipset and 3GB RAM. It also offers users a dual 13MP and 2MP rear camera system, combined with a 24MP selfie camera that offers AI capabilities. Included in these AI tools is a beauty mode that allows for a variety of adjustments, such as skin smoothing, acne removal, and teeth whitening. The Honor 10 Lite sports a 6.21-inch 2,340 x 1,080 screen which is placed in a bezel-less design. Other specifications include a 3,400mAh battery, Huawei’s EMUI 9.0 operating system (based on Android 9.0), and 64GB storage. The Honor 10 Lite comes in five colours – Sky Blue, Sapphire Blue, Midnight Black, White, and Shiny Red – and will sell exclusively through Vodacom for R4,599 from 5 April 2019. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-300848 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3-640x340.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="340" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3-640x340.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3-600x319.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3-768x408.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3-1200x638.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-3.jpg 1212w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-300850 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-2-640x340.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="340" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-2-640x340.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Honor-10-Lite-2-600x319.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Ho